message: The most reliable strategy I found was to combine one artificial soft item with one natural hard item (e.g., 'yarn' + 'bark'). This typically creates an item worth 30 points. Then, use the 'frame' tool on this combined item. This consistently resulted in a 50-point item for me. The 'frame' tool is a one-time use, and framing an already framed item will break the frame. Avoid cutting hard items and be cautious about framing after achieving 55 points, as it might not increase the value further or could even lower it.
